COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x130
STRING: The far end of the hallway.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13c
STRING: I walked towards the practice room where Fal was
supposed to be waiting.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x152
STRING: The complexity of music is so profound that it is all but
impossible to judge things based on just one recital.

STRING: So I decided to make more time to practice with her, as
I didn't have enough to go on to make a decision about
whether or not we could be partners.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x188
STRING: Of course, I also genuinely enjoyed our last session

STRING: Fal heard the faint sound of my knock, and waved her
hand at me through the door's small window.

STRING: [Fal] “Come in.”

STRING: Upon entering the slightly warm room, Fal greeted me

STRING: [Fal] “I see you decided to come.”

STRING: [Chris] “Yeah... You know how it is, there are a lot of

STRING: [Chris] “I see...”

STRING: She said it so directly, and I felt a slight pang of

STRING: One reason I didn't have many friends was my
personality, and I'd half given up because of it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2fc
STRING: I had Asino, Torta, and...

STRING: And that's where my list of friends suddenly stopped.

STRING: I didn't want to misinterpret her obvious friendliness

STRING: However, I did feel that we were on the same page

STRING: [Fal] “Well then, shall we get straight into it?”

STRING: [Chris] “Of course, that's what we're here for.”

STRING: [Fal] “Yes, so about that...

STRING: We're running out of time,
so I think it may be best for us to get

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3ca
STRING: [Chris] “So you mean we should focus on playing

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3fc
STRING: [Fal] “Yes. Not just for me,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x440
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, I think you're right.”

STRING: [Fal] “And also so that we can iron out the little things,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x47e
STRING: [Chris] “Okay, let's give it a try.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x494
STRING: I took the score she gave me out of my bag, and placed
it on the music stand.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4a0
STRING: Fal had already finished her vocal exercises, so she was
probably just waiting for me to get ready.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4b6
STRING: She seemed quite relaxed, sitting there watching me set
up my Fortelle.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4e0
STRING: I played a few notes on my Fortelle, and she matched
her voice to them as we did our final tuning.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4fe
STRING: We both nodded to each other slightly, as one does at
the start of a song, and began our performance.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5ae
STRING: [Fal] “Phew... That sounded great.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5c4
STRING: While catching her breath, she immediately spoke after
she finished singing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5d0
STRING: I felt embarrassed at receiving such a direct
compliment, but also slightly happy at the same time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5e6
STRING: [Chris] “You know that... I'm not good with
compliments.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x618
STRING: [Fal] “I know.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x646
STRING: But, I said it because I felt great
singing just now.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x652
STRING: It seemed like she really enjoyed singing, from the
bottom of her heart, just like Phorni did.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x668
STRING: Unable to find the right response, I shook the fatigue
out of my hands and waited for her to continue
speaking.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x67e
STRING: Fal picked up on this, and with a slightly mischievous
smile she continued.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6b0
STRING: [Fal] “...Okay. I guess if I were to nit-pick, I'd say we
probably need to improve our sense of timing for the
ritardando and the fermata.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6da
STRING: The ritardando, for gradually reducing the tempo, and
the fermata, for finishing a prolonged note.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6f0
STRING: Both of these don't have any deeper significance, and in
actuality it's often up to the performer to decide how
much the tempo needs to change, or how long a note
is prolonged.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x710
STRING: When performing in an orchestra, one just has to obey
the rhythm created by the conductor and their baton.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x726
STRING: But, in cases like this for a duo or a quartet, the
performers have to keep time with each other and
judge the timing themselves.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x74e
STRING: [Fal] “But this is something we can work out by just
practicing more together...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x76e
STRING: [Chris] “Alright.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7a0
STRING: [Fal] “Anyway, do you have any comments, Chris?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7b6
STRING: [Chris] “Nothing in particular, no...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7cc
STRING: I wasn't sure how much she'd been practicing, but it
seemed she knew everything that was on the score.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7e2
STRING: Seeing her close her eyes and sing without faltering,
despite actually having the score in her hands, showed
that she was already beyond the realm of being
just a 'student'.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x814
STRING: [Fal] “Really?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x82a
STRING: [Chris] “Really.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x85c
STRING: [Fal] “Hrm...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x872
STRING: Perhaps she was doubtful of me, as she looked into my
eyes trying to find some kind of hint, but then flashed a
big smile.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8a4
STRING: [Fal] “Thanks!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8ba
STRING: [Chris] “...No problem. But is there really nothing else
you think I need to improve?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8f6
STRING: [Fal] “Nope.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x90c
STRING: [Chris] “Really?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x93e
STRING: [Fal] “Well...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x954
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x986
STRING: [Fal] “Do you want to hear it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x99c
STRING: I was just expecting her to reassure me, but...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9b2
STRING: [Chris] “Uh... Yeah, sure.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9e4
STRING: [Fal] “In that case, there's a couple of things I noticed.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9fa
STRING: I never thought that I was perfect but... Ugh.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa06
STRING: [Chris] “I'd like to know, thanks.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa38
STRING: [Fal] “Okay. First, could you take a look at page four of
the score? In the second bar of the second section.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa58
STRING: [Chris] “Sure... Okay.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa7e
STRING: What she pointed out to me was shockingly accurate.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa8c
STRING: From just one or two rehearsals together, she was able
to see exactly what I was lacking.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xaa4
STRING: And they were all things that Ms. Cordell had told me to

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xabc
STRING: I still hadn't fixed these things, but I was doing my very
best to consciously work on them when performing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xad2
STRING: I wondered how much time had passed.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xade
STRING: Without realizing it myself, I had been listening intently
to everything Fal said.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xaf6
STRING: I may have been just more than a little influenced by her
and the way she eloquently and devotedly spoke about
music.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb30
STRING: [Fal] “...And I think that's about everything.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb46
STRING: By the time she had finished, she was almost as out of
breath as she was after singing.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb5c
STRING: In my head I was replaying everything she said so as not

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb8e
STRING: [Fal] “Chris...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xba4
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbd6
STRING: [Fal] “Umm... I'm Sorry.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbec
STRING: [Chris] “W-What about?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc0a
STRING: [Fal] “About suddenly pointing out all those things...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc20
STRING: [Chris] “Oh, that? I don't mind at all. In fact, I really

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc5c
STRING: [Fal] “You appreciate it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc72
STRING: [Chris] “Everything you said, Ms. Cordell had already

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcae
STRING: [Fal] “Right. I've seen her around.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcdc
STRING: So, what about her?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xce8
STRING: [Chris] “She almost never repeats the things she says,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd1a
STRING: [Fal] “Oh, I see.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd30
STRING: [Chris] “And now today, I realized that I haven't

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd6c
STRING: [Fal] “In that case, I'm glad I helped.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd9a
STRING: I don't think
it would hurt for Ms. Cordell to repeat things,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdb0
STRING: Fal didn't seem to approve of Ms. Cordell's methods.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdbc
STRING: I didn't mind, though.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdc8
STRING: [Chris] “I think it's because she knows I am making an
effort to improve...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe04
STRING: [Fal] “I see...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe32
STRING: That's good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe3e
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, which is why I don't mind. But, clearly I'm
not quite there yet, so it really helps that you pointed

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe7a
STRING: [Fal] “Well, then... I'm glad to be of service.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe90
STRING: [Chris] “You're a great help.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xec2
STRING: [Fal] “Thanks!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xed8
STRING: [Chris] “I'm supposed to be thanking you, you know.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf0a
STRING: [Fal] “Oh, that's right.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf20
STRING: She responded simply, and with a smile.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf3e
STRING: [Fal] “So, why don't we go again, with me taking extra

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf98
STRING: [Fal] “Phew...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfae
STRING: After she finished singing, Fal took a deep breath and

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfe0
STRING: [Fal] “And that's it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xff6
STRING: [Chris] “Good work.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1028
STRING: [Fal] “Well? Are you getting used to the song?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x103e
STRING: [Chris] “Somewhat, yeah.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1054
STRING: The fact that she asked me probably means there are
some aspects I'm still not good at.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x106a
STRING: And actually, it was true and I knew it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1076
STRING: I was still getting caught up in the score, and
sometimes my fingers couldn't keep up.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1094
STRING: [Fal] “That's good to hear. It's starting to sound quite

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10aa
STRING: [Chris] “Thanks. I can tell some things are still lacking,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10dc
STRING: [Fal] “Hm... I see.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x110a
STRING: I'm sure those things will work themselves out through

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1120
STRING: [Chris] “Is there anything else?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1152
STRING: [Fal] “Let me see... There are a couple of things.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1180
STRING: Could you look at the second page of the score?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1196
STRING: [Chris] “Sure.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11be
STRING: She went on to explain the areas that she was
concerned about.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11d6
STRING: What she pointed out to me was shockingly accurate.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11e4
STRING: From just one or two rehearsals together, she was able
to see exactly what I was lacking.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11fc
STRING: And they were all things that Ms. Cordell had told me to

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1214
STRING: I still hadn't fixed these things, but I was doing my very

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x122a
STRING: I wondered how much time had passed since we

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1236
STRING: Without realizing it myself, I had been listening intently

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x124e
STRING: I may have been just more than a little influenced by
her, and the way she spoke about music with such

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1288
STRING: [Fal] “I think that's about it...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x129e
STRING: [Chris] “Got it. Thanks for all your help.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12d0
STRING: [Fal] “Sorry to suddenly lay all these things on you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12e6
STRING: [Chris] “No no, the fact you point them out makes it a

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1322
STRING: [Fal] “That's a relief, then. Shall we rehearse one more

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1338
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, let's do that.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x136a
STRING: [Fal] “Alright.”

STRING: We finished practicing, and had also packed everything

STRING: It was starting to get dark outside, too.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13f8
STRING: [Fal] “Good work today.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x140e
STRING: [Chris] “You too.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1424
STRING: With our bags now on our shoulders, we headed

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x148a
STRING: [Fal] “I don't have to do anything today,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14b8
STRING: so shall we
head back together?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14c4
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14f6
STRING: [Fal] “Well, I can only go as far as the same spot as last

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1516
STRING: [Chris] “Uh...”

STRING: I had no reason to decline.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1538
STRING: [Chris] “Sure, why not?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1556
STRING: [Fal] “Okay then, shall we?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1576
STRING: I trailed behind Fal, who was walking cheerfully.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15ac
STRING: She didn't have an umbrella today.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15b8
STRING: The rain wasn't exactly heavy today, and we had both
gotten used to living in this town, so it almost felt

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15d8
STRING: Walking so close to her, however, made me feel slightly
guilty about Arie, so it wasn't entirely pleasant.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x15f8
STRING: [Chris] “So, you'll be in the same place on other

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x160e
STRING: Unwilling to show what I was feeling, I just tried to
maintain some harmless topics of conversation.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1624
STRING: But I was aware that I was contradicting myself, as I was

conversation.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x165e
STRING: [Fal] “Yes.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x168c
STRING: I'm sorry I can't practice more.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1698
STRING: [Chris] “That's no problem, but... Do you mind if I ask
why you can't practice?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16ca
STRING: [Fal] “Hm? I have a part-time job.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16e0
STRING: [Chris] “You do?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1712
STRING: [Fal] “On days besides Tuesday and Thursday when I

leave straight away. I have Sundays off, but
Saturdays I work
[Fal] all afternoon.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x173c
STRING: [Chris] “Huh...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1752
STRING: She said it like it was nothing, but it certainly sounded
like a rough schedule.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1768
STRING: [Chris] “W-When do you practice?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x179a
STRING: [Fal] “On days like today, with you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17b0
STRING: [Chris] “Is that it...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17e2
STRING: [Fal] “Like I said, I practice after class in the mornings

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x181a
STRING: I can practice until lunch time on Saturdays
too, and I have all day on Sundays.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1830
STRING: [Chris] “Oh...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1862
STRING: [Fal] “What's wrong?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1878
STRING: [Chris] “Oh nothing, I was just thinking that you're really
working hard.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18aa
STRING: [Fal] “Hm... I guess I am.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18c0
STRING: Unexpectedly, Fal didn't try to be humble, and just

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x18d6
STRING: But for some reason, I was unable to ask her why she

STRING: [Fal] “I wonder, would you like to drop by where I

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1900
STRING: [Chris] “Drop by...? What kind of job do you have?”

STRING: [Fal] “I cook at a trattoria called 'Copert'. I've been

COMMANDS.LABEL: 191e
STRING: [Fal] sometime!”

STRING: [Chris] “I know the place...”

STRING: [Fal] “Oh? Really?”

STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, a friend took me there once.”

STRING: [Fal] “I'm glad to hear that...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1aa8
STRING: [Chris] “You work Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1ada
STRING: [Fal] “Ohh, that's a shame. But, the food was good,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1af0
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah, it was great.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b22
STRING: [Fal] “I'm glad to hear that. I hope you can come by
again sometime, maybe on a day I'm there.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b42
STRING: [Chris] “Ahh... Sure, will do.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b74
STRING: [Fal] “Sure, will do.”

STRING: Fal laughed happily while doing her best impression of

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1bb2
STRING: [Fal] “Okay, it's about time for me.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1bc8
STRING: [Chris] “Oh, see you later, then.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1be6
STRING: [Fal] “Bye!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c00
STRING: Watching Fal cheerfully walk off into the distance, I
imagined the Old District that she lived in.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c16
STRING: She works a part-time job, and devotes her limited free

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c2c
STRING: In the beginning I thought she was just one of those
perfect students that was on a different level to me...

STRING: But I realized that she was more than just that.

STRING: I left the jumble of thoughts I just had in the corner of
